parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to engine smoke and fire, which can result in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially even loss of life.
symptoms: The engine starts spurring or missing
the engine starts smoking
the engine catches fire
the main fuse box ignites.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to potential fires, and damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: Battery leaks
acid spills
burning holes in nearby components (e.g. charcoal canister).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a lack of warning to other drivers or pedestrians, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The horn fails to sound or is inaudible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden lock-up of the steering column can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up while driving
the steering wheel vibrates or makes a popping noise
the vehicle veers off course or crashes
the driver is unable to turn the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motor can cause the windows to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to operate the windows, which can lead to safety issues, such as reduced visibility, and inconvenience.
symptoms: The windows do not roll up or down
the windows are stuck in a particular position
the windows make unusual noises or vibrations when operating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the sun roof can cause the sun roof to become stuck or fall, which can lead to safety issues, such as distraction or injury, and inconvenience.
symptoms: The sun roof does not open or close
the sun roof is stuck in a particular position
the sun roof makes unusual noises or vibrations when operating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially in heavy rain or snow conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working
the windshield wipers work intermittently
the windshield wipers make unusual noises or vibrations when operating.
